---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ToolPageCta from '../../components/ToolPageCta.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';

const faq = [
  {
    question: "What is Weaviate and what makes it different?",
    answer: "Weaviate is an open-source vector database with built-in hybrid search (BM25 keyword + vector similarity). Unlike Pinecone, it is self-hostable, supports native vectorizer modules (you don't need to pre-compute embeddings separately), and exposes a GraphQL API. It also supports multi-tenancy, cross-references between objects, and generative search via LLM integrations."
  },
  {
    question: "What are Weaviate vectorizer modules?",
    answer: "Weaviate modules auto-vectorize your data at ingestion time. text2vec-openai calls the OpenAI embeddings API, text2vec-cohere uses Cohere embed, text2vec-huggingface uses HuggingFace Inference API, and text2vec-transformers runs a local sentence transformer model. You configure the module at class level — Weaviate handles embedding automatically on every insert."
  },
  {
    question: "How does hybrid search work in Weaviate?",
    answer: "Weaviate hybrid search combines BM25 (sparse keyword retrieval) with dense vector similarity using a Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF) or weighted sum algorithm. You pass an alpha parameter between 0 (pure BM25) and 1 (pure vector). A value of 0.5 blends both equally. Hybrid search outperforms pure vector search for queries with specific keywords, product names, or IDs."
  },
  {
    question: "What is multi-tenancy in Weaviate?",
    answer: "Weaviate multi-tenancy isolates data per tenant at the shard level. Each tenant gets its own shard which can be independently activated, deactivated (offloaded to cold storage), or deleted. This enables SaaS applications to serve thousands of customers from one cluster while keeping data isolated and controlling storage costs by offloading inactive tenants."
  },
  {
    question: "Weaviate Cloud vs self-hosted: which should I choose?",
    answer: "Weaviate Cloud (WCD) is the managed SaaS option — zero infrastructure work, automatic upgrades, and a free sandbox tier. Self-hosted via Docker or Kubernetes gives you full control over hardware, data residency, and cost at scale. For production workloads under 10M vectors with a small team, WCD is often faster to ship. For >100M vectors or strict compliance requirements, self-hosted on your own VPC is more cost-effective."
  },
  {
    question: "Can Weaviate replace a traditional search engine like Elasticsearch?",
    answer: "Weaviate can replace Elasticsearch for semantic search use cases where understanding query intent matters more than keyword matching. It has BM25 support for keyword scenarios too. However, Elasticsearch has a more mature ecosystem for log analytics, complex aggregations, and enterprise search. For AI-native applications — RAG, semantic document search, recommendation — Weaviate is often the better fit."
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Weaviate: Open-Source Vector Database with Hybrid Search"
  description="Complete guide to Weaviate vector database — schema classes, text2vec-openai/cohere vectorizer modules, hybrid search (BM25 + vector), GraphQL query API, multi-tenancy, self-hosted vs Weaviate Cloud, and comparison table."
  tool="Weaviate, vector database, hybrid search, GraphQL, open-source vector DB"
  faq={faq}
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"WebPage","name":"Weaviate: Open-Source Vector Database with Hybrid Search","url":"https://devplaybook.cc/tools/weaviate","description":"Complete guide to Weaviate — hybrid search, vectorizer modules, GraphQL API, multi-tenancy, and self-hosted vs cloud deployment."})} />

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Weaviate: Open-Source Vector Database with Hybrid Search</h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted mb-6">Weaviate is an open-source vector database that combines semantic vector search with BM25 keyword search (hybrid search), auto-vectorization via pluggable modules, and a flexible GraphQL API. It is production-ready for RAG pipelines, semantic search, and multi-tenant SaaS applications — self-hosted or on Weaviate Cloud.</p>

  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 text-sm text-text-muted flex-wrap">
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Hybrid search (BM25 + vector)</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Auto-vectorizer modules</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> GraphQL &amp; REST API</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Multi-tenancy</span>
    <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Open source (Apache 2.0)</span>
  </div>

  <ToolPageCta />

  <!-- Schema & Collection -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Defining a Weaviate Schema (Class + Properties)</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">In Weaviate, data is organized into classes (like database tables). Each class has typed properties and a vectorizer configuration.</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-4"><code class="text-green-400">import weaviate
from weaviate.classes.config import Configure, Property, DataType

client = weaviate.connect_to_weaviate_cloud(
    cluster_url="https://YOUR-CLUSTER.weaviate.network",
    auth_credentials=weaviate.auth.AuthApiKey("YOUR_API_KEY")
)

# Create a collection with OpenAI vectorizer
client.collections.create(
    name="Article",
    vectorizer_config=Configure.Vectorizer.text2vec_openai(
        model="text-embedding-3-small",
        dimensions=1536,
    ),
    generative_config=Configure.Generative.openai(model="gpt-4o-mini"),
    properties=[
        Property(name="title",   data_type=DataType.TEXT),
        Property(name="content", data_type=DataType.TEXT),
        Property(name="category",data_type=DataType.TEXT),
        Property(name="pubDate", data_type=DataType.DATE),
    ]
)

# Insert objects — Weaviate auto-generates the embedding
articles = client.collections.get("Article")
with articles.batch.dynamic() as batch:
    batch.add_object(&#123;
        "title":    "Introduction to RAG",
        "content":  "Retrieval-augmented generation combines search with LLMs...",
        "category": "ai",
        "pubDate":  "2024-01-15T00:00:00Z"
    &#125;)

client.close()</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Hybrid Search -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Hybrid Search: BM25 + Vector</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Hybrid search combines dense vector similarity with sparse BM25 keyword matching. The alpha parameter controls the blend.</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-4"><code class="text-green-400">from weaviate.classes.query import Filter, MetadataQuery

articles = client.collections.get("Article")

# Hybrid search — alpha=0.7 weights vector search more than BM25
results = articles.query.hybrid(
    query="how does retrieval augmented generation work",
    alpha=0.7,              # 0 = pure BM25, 1 = pure vector
    limit=5,
    filters=Filter.by_property("category").equal("ai"),
    return_metadata=MetadataQuery(score=True)
)

for obj in results.objects:
    print(f"&#123;obj.metadata.score:.4f&#125; | &#123;obj.properties['title']&#125;")

# Pure vector search (nearText auto-vectorizes the query)
results_vec = articles.query.near_text(
    query="semantic search techniques",
    limit=3,
    filters=Filter.by_property("category").equal("ai")
)

# Generative search — retrieve + LLM in one call
results_gen = articles.generate.near_text(
    query="RAG architectures",
    single_prompt="Summarize this article in one sentence: &#123;content&#125;",
    limit=3
)
for obj in results_gen.objects:
    print(obj.generated)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Multi-tenancy -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Multi-Tenancy Configuration</h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted mb-4">Enable multi-tenancy at class creation. Each tenant gets an isolated shard that can be independently managed.</p>
    <pre class="bg-bg-card border border-border rounded-xl p-4 text-sm font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-4"><code class="text-green-400">from weaviate.classes.config import Configure
from weaviate.classes.tenants import Tenant, TenantActivityStatus

# Create a multi-tenant collection
client.collections.create(
    name="CustomerDocs",
    multi_tenancy_config=Configure.multi_tenancy(enabled=True),
    vectorizer_config=Configure.Vectorizer.text2vec_openai()
)

col = client.collections.get("CustomerDocs")

# Add tenants
col.tenants.create([
    Tenant(name="tenant-acme"),
    Tenant(name="tenant-globex"),
])

# All CRUD operations are scoped to a tenant
tenant_col = col.with_tenant("tenant-acme")
tenant_col.data.insert(&#123;"content": "ACME private document"&#125;)

# Offload inactive tenant to cold storage (saves cost)
col.tenants.update([
    Tenant(name="tenant-acme", activity_status=TenantActivityStatus.INACTIVE)
])

# Delete a tenant and all its data
col.tenants.remove(["tenant-acme"])</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison Table -->
  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Weaviate vs Pinecone vs Qdrant vs Chroma</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm min-w-[640px]">
        <thead>
          <tr class="text-text-muted text-xs uppercase border-b border-border">
            <th class="text-left pb-3 pr-4 font-medium">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-3 pr-4 font-medium">Weaviate</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-3 pr-4 font-medium">Pinecone</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-3 pr-4 font-medium">Qdrant</th>
            <th class="text-left pb-3 font-medium">Chroma</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-text-muted">
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Open source</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">Yes</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">No</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">Yes</td><td class="py-3 text-green-500">Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Hybrid search</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">BM25 + vector</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Limited</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">Sparse + dense</td><td class="py-3">Vector only</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Auto-vectorize</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">Yes (modules)</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">No</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">No</td><td class="py-3">Yes (embedding fn)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Query API</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">GraphQL + REST</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">REST / SDK</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">REST / gRPC</td><td class="py-3">Python SDK</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Multi-tenancy</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">Shard-level</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Namespaces</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Collections</td><td class="py-3">Collections</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Managed cloud</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Weaviate Cloud</td><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-green-500">Yes (serverless)</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Qdrant Cloud</td><td class="py-3">No</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text">Best for</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Hybrid RAG, SaaS</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Fast managed setup</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">High perf self-host</td><td class="py-3">Local dev, prototypes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FaqSection faq={faq} />
  <ToolPageCta currentTool="Weaviate Vector Database Guide" relatedTags={['ai', 'vector-database', 'embeddings', 'rag', 'semantic-search', 'hybrid-search']} />
</BaseLayout>
